# Structural Rules
- No folder restructuring.
- No refactors without explicit request.
- Only modify files relevant to the current task — list any file 
  not previously discussed before changing it.
- After implementation: list changed files and why.
- After implementation: provide a short manual smoke test checklist.

# Context Discipline
Before performing any task, read context.md.
Respect fixed decisions and current focus.
Do not propose structural changes that contradict context.md 
  unless explicitly requested.
After completing a task, update only the Current State section 
  in context.md. Keep updates concise (max 3–4 lines).
Do not modify other sections of context.md unless explicitly requested.

# Autonomy Level 1 (Refactor-with-Plan)
- Small refactors are allowed if you first provide a short plan (max 5 bullets) and list all files to be changed.
- Do not modify persistence / migration / import-export logic (src/storage.js, src/migrations.js) unless explicitly requested.
- If you touch any of those high-risk files, stop and ask for confirmation first.